<!DOCTYPE document PUBLIC "-//Apache Software Foundation//DTD XDOC 1.0//EN" "http://maven.apache.org/dtd/xdoc_1_0.dtd">
<document>
  <properties>
    <title>Release notes</title>
  </properties>
  <body>
    <section name="Compatibility">
      <table>
        <tr>
          <th>Plugin version</th>
          <th>Hippo CMS Release version</th>
        </tr>
        <tr>
          <td>1.01.xx</td>
          <td>7.7.x, 7.8.x, 7.9.x</td>
        </tr>
        <tr>
          <td>0.xx.xx</td>
          <td>7.7.x, 7.8.x</td>
        </tr>
      </table>
    </section>
    <section name="Release Notes">
      <subsection name="1.01.00">
        <ul>
          <li>
            Externalizing JTidy properties file in order to allow users to set any JTidy configurations
            (e.g, adding unknown tags which cannot be tidied by default).
            <br/>
            Thanks to Eray Konur!
          </li>
          <li>Fixing documentation about how to set font files in HtmlPDFRenderingFilter filter configuration in web.xml</li>
          <li>Upgrade the demo project to base itself on Hippo CMS 7.9 (but the module should work on Hippo CMS 7.8, too.)</li>
        </ul>
      </subsection>
      <subsection name="0.01.01">
        <ul>
          <li>Fixing License Headers</li>
        </ul>
      </subsection>
      <subsection name="0.01.00">
        <ul>
          <li>Initial Release</li>
          <li>HTML to XHTML transformation by using JTidy</li>
          <li>Transforming image tags (&lt;img&gt;) to use local absolute URLs in order to embed images in the generated PDF output</li>
          <li>Transforming link tags (&lt;a&gt;) to use external absolute URLs in order to enable linking in the generated PDF output</li>
          <li>Transforming XHTML to PDF by using Flying Saucer</li>
          <li>Site documentation</li>
        </ul>
      </subsection>
    </section>
  </body>
</document>